  </div>

  <div class="col-md-7">
    <h1>Marion B. Bracy</h1>
    <h5 class="text-muted">Board Member</h5>
    <hr>

    <p>Brother Marion B. Bracy is a lifelong servant leader initiated into Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity, Inc. on November 20, 1981, through the Beta Phi Chapter at Dillard University.</p>
    <p>He served in multiple Southwest Region leadership roles including Election Committee, Awards Committee, and Acting Vice President of the Southwest Region.</p>
    <p>He was appointed national leader under multiple General Presidents and served as Chairman of the College Brothers Commission, authoring the first College Brothers Advisors Handbook.</p>
    <p>He became the youngest elected President of Sigma Lambda Chapter and led major initiatives including Project Alpha and national convention hosting.</p>
    <p>Professionally, he has held senior leadership roles at Dillard University and Xavier University, helping secure over $100M in FEMA recovery funding after Katrina and Rita.</p>
    <p>He currently serves as Vice President for Facilities and Real Estate Management at Dillard University.</p>
  </div>
</div>

</div>

